{"correction_id":"core-coverage-qbnr-page-date-20260712","op":"patch_payload","record_id":"source_mta-queens-bus-network-redesign-service-changes","guards":{"payload":{"published_date_normalized":"2025-06-29","published_date_provenance":"staged_metadata"}},"patch":{"set":{"published_date_normalized":null,"published_date_precision":"unknown","published_date_provenance":"unknown_not_evidenced","retrieved_at":"2026-06-07T01:03:14.507Z","retrieved_date_normalized":"2026-06-07","retrieval_provenance":"captured_metadata"}},"cascade":[],"reason":"The staged documentDate was the Queens redesign Phase 1 effective date, not page publication metadata. The official page exposes no datePublished/dateModified value; publication is therefore unknown, while the immutable capture metadata supports the retrieval timestamp.","source_decision":"data/quality/acquisition/receipts/q7-route-redesign-2025-08-31.json","reviewed_at":"2026-07-12T15:00:00Z","provenance":"human"}
{"correction_id":"core-coverage-q25-route-scope-20260713","op":"patch_payload","record_id":"route_q25-queens","guards":{"payload":{"route_id":"Q25","routes":["Q25"],"route_type_normalized":"bus","route_type":"local bus","service_variant":"local","_merged_field_values":{"route_type_normalized":["bus","local","limited_stop"],"route_type":["local bus","local","limited","Local"],"service_variant":["local","limited_stop"],"description":["Q25 LTD: Jamaica to College Point via Parsons Blvd/Kissena Blvd","Q25: Jamaica to College Point, part of Parsons Blvd/Kissena Blvd corridor future SBS candidates","SBS candidate route: Jamaica to College Point on Parsons Blvd/Kissena Blvd corridor","Bus service on Kissena/Parsons Boulevards between Flushing and Queens College/Jamaica; part of Flushing to Jamaica SBS study","Runs from College Point to Downtown Jamaica, connecting Linden Hill, Flushing, Kissena Park, Pomonok"]},"route_record_scope":"split_candidate","route_record_scope_reason":"merged_service_variant_conflict"}},"patch":{"set":{"route_record_scope":"true_route","route_record_scope_reason":"reviewed_current_route_historical_limited_pattern_lifecycle_compatible"}},"cascade":[],"reason":"Nine accepted observations describe one Q25 umbrella route across local and historical limited-stop service-pattern contexts. The current GTFS reference contains one Q25 route, and official MTA redesign evidence says current Q25 routing continues while Q25 Limited is discontinued on 2025-06-29. The merged local/limited literals are therefore lifecycle-compatible context, not two unresolved current route identities.","source_decision":"data/quality/acquisition/receipts/q25-route-scope-2025-06-29.json","reviewed_at":"2026-07-13T00:00:00Z","provenance":"human"}
{"correction_id":"core-coverage-q52-route-scope-20260713","op":"patch_payload","record_id":"route_q52-sbs-queens","guards":{"payload":{"route_id":"Q52 SBS","route_name":"Q52 SBS","route_label":"Q52 SBS","routes":["Q52 SBS"],"route_type":"Select Bus Service","route_type_normalized":"select_bus_service","service_variant":"sbs","route_record_scope":"split_candidate","route_record_scope_reason":"merged_slash_route_surface"}},"patch":{"set":{"route_id":"Q52-SBS","routes":["Q52"],"route_record_scope":"true_route","route_record_scope_reason":"reviewed_q52_ltd_sbs_lifecycle_and_shared_corridor_slash_context_compatible"}},"cascade":[],"reason":"Fifty-five accepted observations from 47 official sources describe one Q52 route across historical Limited and current SBS contexts. Current GTFS independently identifies Q52+ and Q53+, the official 2025 redesign row names only Q52, and official lifecycle evidence uses Q52/Q53 wording for the coordinated Woodhaven/Cross Bay program while preserving the separate route numbers. The merged slash literal is therefore shared-corridor context, not an unresolved combined route identity.","source_decision":"data/quality/acquisition/receipts/q52-route-scope-2025-08-31.json","reviewed_at":"2026-07-13T00:00:00Z","provenance":"human"}
{"correction_id":"core-coverage-q20a-route-scope-20260713","op":"patch_payload","record_id":"route_q20-2014-10-07-flushing-jamaica","guards":{"payload":{"route_id":"Q20A","route_label":"Q20A/Q20B","route_name":"Q20A/B","route_record_scope":"aggregate_list_context","route_record_scope_reason":"slash_route_surface"}},"patch":{"set":{"route_record_scope":"true_route","route_record_scope_reason":"reviewed_historical_q20a_lifecycle_distinct_from_q20b_and_current_q20"}},"cascade":[],"reason":"The canonical record's primary route identity is Q20A, Q20B already has a separate canonical route record, and official 2025 Queens Bus Network Redesign evidence independently states that Q20A and Q20B ended while a newly named Q20 started. Older Q20A/B and Q20AB literals remain preserved evidence context, but are not authority to merge the historical Q20A identity with Q20B or the replacement Q20.","source_decision":"data/quality/acquisition/receipts/q15a-q20a-terminal-route-identity-2025.json","reviewed_at":"2026-07-13T12:00:00Z","provenance":"human"}
